<h3>Course Description</h3>
<ul>
In this seminar course, 
we will read, discuss and critique papers related
to parallel architectures and parallel computing.
The topics of the papers will include:
<ul>
<li>
Resource management in CMPs
<li>
Fault tolerance in parallel systems
<li>
Memory issues, and particularly PRAMs
<li>
Power management issues
<li>
Parallel programming models
<li>
Interconnection networks (including NoC)
<li>
Parallel algorithms
<li>
Cloud and grid computing
<li>
GPUs and heterogeneous processing
</ul>

<h3>Requirements and grading:</h3>

A student taking the course for audit (S/N grade) will have to read and present papers to earn an S grade. A student taking the course for a letter grade
will additionally have to complete a class project. The project will account
for 50% of the grade.

<h3>Course 
<a href = "progress.html">
Schedule:
</a>
</h3>
The course consists of
<ul>
<li> 
Introductory presentations by the instructor
<li>
Presentations by students. 
<ul>
Each week, three papers will be presented. A paper will be presented in 25 minutes followed by a 20 minutes discussion.
One student will be the presenter and two/three students will lead the discussion.
Each of the presenter and the discussants of a paper will have to write a short review/critique of the paper (due before class).
</ul>
<li>
Presentations and Demonstrations of Class Projects
<ul>
Each student will present a proposal and a final demonstration of a project. Up to two students can collaborate on the same project.
</ul>
</ul>

